One of South Africa&rsquo;s most wanted fugitives, facing a R500 million fraud and corruption charge, was found dead in his hotel room this morning, the Hawks said.&nbsp;Adriaan Van Vuuren, 44, is believed to have suffocated himself by using gas inside the hotel room, Hawks spokesperson Ndivhuwo Mulamu said in a statement.&nbsp;Hotel staff found his body in the Centurion Lake Hotel when they wanted to clean his room.&nbsp;Van Vuuren checked into the hotel for a one night stay on Wednesday.&nbsp;Van Vuuren is accused of submitting fraudulent claims for IT services required while he was the IT Manager at Trudon, a subsidiary of Telkom.&nbsp;http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/man-accused-of-r500-million-corruption-found-dead-on-hotel-room-floor-20170330